## 🔒 Protection Features

### **1. Backend Protection (API Level)**

The following operations are **blocked** for the main admin account (`admin@example.com`):

| Operation | Endpoint | Protection |
|-----------|----------|------------|
| **Edit User** | `PUT /api/users/{id}` | ✅ **ALLOWED** - Main admin can edit themselves |
| **Delete User** | `DELETE /api/users/{id}` | ❌ **BLOCKED** - Returns error: "Cannot delete the main admin account" |
| **Toggle Status** | `PUT /api/users/{id}` (isActive) | ✅ **ALLOWED** - But prevented from deactivating themselves via self-deactivation check |
| **Change Role** | `PUT /api/users/{id}` (role) | ✅ **ALLOWED** - Main admin can change their own role if needed |
| **Reset Password** | `PUT /api/users/{id}/reset-password` | ✅ **ALLOWED** - Main admin can reset their own password |

