## 💡 Implementation Details

### **Why Email-Based Protection?**

We use `user.email === 'admin@example.com'` instead of checking user ID because:
- ✅ Email is more reliable (won't change)
- ✅ User ID might change in different environments
- ✅ Clear identification of the main admin account
- ✅ Easy to understand and maintain

### **Why Both Backend and Frontend Protection?**

- **Backend Protection**: Security enforcement (cannot be bypassed)
- **Frontend Protection**: User experience (clear visual feedback)

**Defense in Depth**: Even if someone bypasses the frontend, the backend will reject the request.

